article.description: — Montre' Gipson's 14 points helped Charlotte defeat Appalachian State 71-62 on Friday night.
article.headline: Gipson's 14 lead Charlotte past Appalachian State 71-62
article.linkText: Gipson's 14 lead Charlotte past Appalachian State 71-62
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — Montre' Gipson's 14 points helped Charlotte defeat Appalachian State 71-62 on Friday night. Gipson added eight rebounds and seven assists for the 49ers (7-2). Igor Milicic Jr. scored 11 points and added seven rebounds. Jackson Threadgill was 4 of 10 shooting (2 for 4 from distance) to finish with 10 points. The Mountaineers (5-4) were led by Christopher Mantis, who posted 25 points. CJ Huntley added 11 points and two blocks for Appalachian State. In addition, Dibaji Walker had six points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
